result.execSummary:
The defendant Randy S Doepke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Remove Vehicle's Major Parts w/o Consent, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(5).
  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

08:40 AM; Case called for Plea and Sentencing.  Defendant Randy S Doepke in court, in custody, with attorney Jessica A Klein.   Randy P. Sitzberger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Parties advise they are prepared to proceed to plea and sentencing today.  
Atty. Sitzberger outlines the offer.  
Atty. Klein confirms the offer as placed on the record.
Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  
Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Counts 1 & 3.  
Court finds defendant guilty of Counts 1 & 3.  
Counts 2 & 4 are dismissed and read in.

Atty. Sitzberger presents sentencing arguments.
Atty. Klein presents sentencing arguments, and confirms they are stipulating to the amount of restitution.
Defendant presents statements.

The Court Orders the Following:

COUNT 1
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

3 Years Imprisonment 
-	1 Year & 6 Months of Initial Confinement
-	1 Year & 6 Months of Extended Supervision

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program

Term of Probation: 3 Years
Conditions of Probation/Extended Supervision:
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-	Follow any conditions deemed appropriate by Agent;
-	No contact with any victim or business listed in the Criminal Complaint;
-	AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	No Use or Possession of CBD products;
-	No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctors prescription;
-	No use of possession of vaping products;
-	Take Thinking for a Change Course;
-	Mental health Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended.

Condition Time: 6 Months Straight Time to commence forthwith. (23 Days Credit to be applied to Condition time - Concurrent with sentence in Count 3)

RESTITUTION: $232.80  to be paid to Absolute Quality Glass.

FINE or COSTS: Waived by the Court.

DNA Surcharge: $250.00

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of probation. Failure to pay; will result in a civil judgment.

Felony warnings, immigration warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.  

COUNT 3

90 Days Straight Time (Concurent with Condition time in Count 1)

DNA Surcharge: $200.00

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of probation in Count 1. Failure to pay; will result in a civil judgment.
